HEADWORD: Cutty
<hw>Cut"ty</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧t"t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Ir. &
Gael. <ets>cut</ets> a short tail, <ets>cutach</ets> bobtailed. See
<er>Cut</er>.]</ety> <def>Short; <as>as, a <ex>cutty</ex> knife; a
<ex>cutty</ex> sark</as>.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

